<h2>What's in the toolkit</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="{{ '/language/' | url }}">The grigson format</a> — a readable plain-text chord chart language with sections, keys, time signatures, repeats, and volta brackets</li>
  <li><a href="{{ '/renderers/custom-elements/' | url }}">Custom elements</a> — drop <code>&lt;grigson-chart&gt;</code> into any HTML page for live rendering with optional transposition</li>
  <li><a href="{{ '/renderers/svg/' | url }}">SVG renderer</a> — produce publication-quality SVG for embedding in web pages or exporting</li>
  <li><a href="{{ '/renderers/text/' | url }}">Text renderer</a> — round-trip <code>.chart</code> output; use with the CLI for transposition pipelines</li>
  <li><a href="{{ '/cli/' | url }}">CLI</a> — normalise, transpose, and validate <code>.chart</code> files from the command line</li>
  <li><a href="{{ '/playground/' | url }}">Playground</a> — live editor with syntax highlighting, normalisation, and URL sharing</li>
</ul>
